# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath8
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah had watched Samayra leave, walking back to the royal quarters to meet with her father the Shah."
    new "Sarah had watched Samayra leave, walking back to the royal quarters to meet with her father the Shah."

    old "Not long after she left, Sarah spotted Xan walking back across the hall towards her."
    new "Not long after she left, Sarah spotted Xan walking back across the hall towards her."

    old "Nice to see you again as well."
    new "Nice to see you again as well."

    old "The council went as well as could be hoped, but the Shah is still acting cagey."
    new "The council went as well as could be hoped, but the Shah is still acting cagey."

    old "Meaning?"
    new "Meaning?"

    old "I asked him to show me the location of the vault, but he flatly refused. He knows that is the leverage keeping us here, and he's afraid to give it up before we make good on our end."
    new "I asked him to show me the location of the vault, but he flatly refused. He knows that is the leverage keeping us here, and he's afraid to give it up before we make good on our end."

    old "He's not entirely wrong to assume that."
    new "He's not entirely wrong to assume that."

    old "No, but it is still a problem for us."
    new "No, but it is still a problem for us."

    old "If he gives up the vault before we deliver on our end, he's afraid we'll leave. But if we deliver before he does, whose to say he'll be true to his word?"
    new "If he gives up the vault before we deliver on our end, he's afraid we'll leave. But if we deliver before he does, whose to say he'll be true to his word?"

    old "I've managed to make him promise to take me to the vault after tomorrow."
    new "I've managed to make him promise to take me to the vault after tomorrow."

    old "Tomorrow?"
    new "Tomorrow?"

    old "That's when they think the Mythran army will launch their attack."
    new "That's when they think the Mythran army will launch their attack."

    old "She knew the Mythran army would attack, and likely that it would be soon, but tomorrow was still earlier than she had considered possible."
    new "She knew the Mythran army would attack, and likely that it would be soon, but tomorrow was still earlier than she had considered possible."

    old "That's fast."
    new "That's fast."

    old "It likely won't be a full out attack. They'll start by launching some smaller skirmishes, see if there are any weak points in the defense."
    new "It likely won't be a full out attack. They'll start by launching some smaller skirmishes, see if there are any weak points in the defense."

    old "And? Are there any weak points in the defense?"
    new "And? Are there any weak points in the defense?"

    old "Xan grunted."
    new "Xan grunted."

    old "The entire city is one giant weak point. It won't be long before the Mythran forces realize that, then their entire army will follow."
    new "The entire city is one giant weak point. It won't be long before the Mythran forces realize that, then their entire army will follow."

    old "Doesn't Bagrad have the advantage of its massive walls?"
    new "Doesn't Bagrad have the advantage of its massive walls?"

    old "Sarah had seen the great walls that encircled Bagrad, rising up so near to the sky that they cast a shadow across the city."
    new "Sarah had seen the great walls that encircled Bagrad, rising up so near to the sky that they cast a shadow across the city."

    old "The great walls are nothing but an illusion. The Shah doesn't have the manpower to guard them on all sides. Most sections have no soldiers at all."
    new "The great walls are nothing but an illusion. The Shah doesn't have the manpower to guard them on all sides. Most sections have no soldiers at all."

    old "Even with all his troops clustered, they are still fewer than the Mythran host. Which isn't even counting their auxillary troops, mercenary troops from all over."
    new "Even with all his troops clustered, they are still fewer than the Mythran host. Which isn't even counting their auxillary troops, mercenary troops from all over."

    old "Sarah listened as Xan painted a bleak picture."
    new "Sarah listened as Xan painted a bleak picture."

    old "So what then? The city is doomed?"
    new "So what then? The city is doomed?"

    old "Almost certainly, but there are some options left. So long as we can keep them off for a day, the Shah will show us the vault, and we have what we came for."
    new "Almost certainly, but there are some options left. So long as we can keep them off for a day, the Shah will show us the vault, and we have what we came for."

    old "What are our options."
    new "What are our options."

    old "Xan paused, seemingly trying to find the right words."
    new "Xan paused, seemingly trying to find the right words."

    old "The Bagrad army will cluster near the central gate. If the Mythran army wants to enter the city, they will have to pass through it."
    new "The Bagrad army will cluster near the central gate. If the Mythran army wants to enter the city, they will have to pass through it."

    old "The main square behind it will be used as a funnel. With the edges secured, the Mythran army will become trapped behind the gate."
    new "The main square behind it will be used as a funnel. With the edges secured, the Mythran army will become trapped behind the gate."

    old "Once inside and grouped up...I'll step in."
    new "Once inside and grouped up...I'll step in."

    old "You're talking about taking on an entire army, by yourself."
    new "You're talking about taking on an entire army, by yourself."

    old "No, not the entire army. I'll rain down enough destruction to make them think there's an army of mages."
    new "No, not the entire army. I'll rain down enough destruction to make them think there's an army of mages."

    old "If the beating is bad enough, they'll fall back, at least for a few days."
    new "If the beating is bad enough, they'll fall back, at least for a few days."

    old "Sarah wanted Xan to see the insanity of this plan."
    new "Sarah wanted Xan to see the insanity of this plan."

    old "There will be hundreds of archers in that army, crossbowmen..."
    new "There will be hundreds of archers in that army, crossbowmen..."

    old "If just a single one gets a lucky shot off, you're done for."
    new "If just a single one gets a lucky shot off, you're done for."

    old "Xan seemed to consider her point, but only for a moment."
    new "Xan seemed to consider her point, but only for a moment."

    old "Don't worry about me, Sarah. I can take care of myself. I can weave barriers to keep myself safe, and it will only be for a moment."
    new "Don't worry about me, Sarah. I can take care of myself. I can weave barriers to keep myself safe, and it will only be for a moment."

    old "He wasn't going to see sense."
    new "He wasn't going to see sense."

    old "And what about me? Do I get to join you in this suicide mission?"
    new "And what about me? Do I get to join you in this suicide mission?"

    old "That's why I wanted to talk to you."
    new "That's why I wanted to talk to you."

    old "Most of the forces will be stationed near the gate, the Shah has no other option if he wants any chance of matching the Mythran army."
    new "Most of the forces will be stationed near the gate, the Shah has no other option if he wants any chance of matching the Mythran army."

    old "That leaves the palace almost entirely undefended. There will be a handful of guards left, but that's it."
    new "That leaves the palace almost entirely undefended. There will be a handful of guards left, but that's it."

    old "A handful of guards...and me."
    new "A handful of guards...and me."

    old "We don't expect the Mythran army to reach the palace, but we can't be sure there won't be smaller vanguard units sneaking behind the main front."
    new "We don't expect the Mythran army to reach the palace, but we can't be sure there won't be smaller vanguard units sneaking behind the main front."

    old "If that's the case, we will abandon every position in the palace, let them overrun it. Every position, except one."
    new "If that's the case, we will abandon every position in the palace, let them overrun it. Every position, except one."

    old "Sarah could see where he was going with this."
    new "Sarah could see where he was going with this."

    old "The royal quarters..."
    new "The royal quarters..."

    old "You catch on quick."
    new "You catch on quick."

    old "It only has one entrance point, through the throne room."
    new "It only has one entrance point, through the throne room."

    old "That's where you will make your stand. No matter what, you have to be ready to incinerate every soldier that steps into that room."
    new "That's where you will make your stand. No matter what, you have to be ready to incinerate every soldier that steps into that room."

    old "Sarah tried to process that strategy."
    new "Sarah tried to process that strategy."

    old "There was a logic that Sarah could detect."
    new "There was a logic that Sarah could detect."

    old "The throne room was large enough to give her space for performing her magics. The open design of the room left few hiding spots for archers."
    new "The throne room was large enough to give her space for performing her magics. The open design of the room left few hiding spots for archers."

    old "The strange, tomb like design, disoriented most who first entered it. It would take a while for the soldiers to even know where she was attacking them from."
    new "The strange, tomb like design, disoriented most who first entered it. It would take a while for the soldiers to even know where she was attacking them from."

    old "In all, it wasn't entirely foolish, at least not on her part."
    new "In all, it wasn't entirely foolish, at least not on her part."

    old "I think it will work..."
    new "I think it will work..."

    old "I still don't think your part in it is very safe..."
    new "I still don't think your part in it is very safe..."

    old "Xan put a hand on her shoulder."
    new "Xan put a hand on her shoulder."

    old "Don't worry about me, I've survived worse. You just make sure to keep yourself safe."
    new "Don't worry about me, I've survived worse. You just make sure to keep yourself safe."

    old "He seemed so serious to Sarah, suddenly."
    new "He seemed so serious to Sarah, suddenly."

    old "Besides, did you manage to do what I asked?"
    new "Besides, did you manage to do what I asked?"

    old "I spoke to her for a bit. She seems friendly enough."
    new "I spoke to her for a bit. She seems friendly enough."

    old "Sarah wanted to hold back from telling Xan everything that had happened."
    new "Sarah wanted to hold back from telling Xan everything that had happened."

    old "It will have to do I guess. We have so much less time than I thought we would have."
    new "It will have to do I guess. We have so much less time than I thought we would have."

    old "To this, Sarah could only agree."
    new "To this, Sarah could only agree."

    old "Two servants suddenly rushed up to them."
    new "Two servants suddenly rushed up to them."

    old "Esteemed guests, we have come to inform you that your rooms have been prepared."
    new "Esteemed guests, we have come to inform you that your rooms have been prepared."

    old "Good, we'll need our sleep for what comes tomorrow. We'll speak before I leave for the gate, I promise."
    new "Good, we'll need our sleep for what comes tomorrow. We'll speak before I leave for the gate, I promise."

    old "With that, one servant took Xan away, and the other motioned for Sarah to follow."
    new "With that, one servant took Xan away, and the other motioned for Sarah to follow."

    old "Sarah began to walk after the servant as he lead her out into the hallways of the palace."
    new "Sarah began to walk after the servant as he lead her out into the hallways of the palace."

    old "Walking some paces ahead of her, the servant wordlessly guided her."
    new "Walking some paces ahead of her, the servant wordlessly guided her."

    old "It was now late, deep into the night. With clouds having gathered, even the stars and the moon offered no reprieve."
    new "It was now late, deep into the night. With clouds having gathered, even the stars and the moon offered no reprieve."

    old "The darkness became deepened by the vast emptiness of the palace."
    new "The darkness became deepened by the vast emptiness of the palace."

    old "It had surprised Sarah when she first came to Bagrad, how the days could be scorching hot, and the nights freezing cold."
    new "It had surprised Sarah when she first came to Bagrad, how the days could be scorching hot, and the nights freezing cold."

    old "This was one such night."
    new "This was one such night."

    old "Her mind drifted towards Samayra."
    new "Her mind drifted towards Samayra."

    old "An image of the girl came to her, a princess all alone in a palace, few friends, walking dark and empty halls, never being allowed to leave."
    new "An image of the girl came to her, a princess all alone in a palace, few friends, walking dark and empty halls, never being allowed to leave."

    old "In a world where so many had so little, it seemed odd to pity a princess, and yet Sarah did."
    new "In a world where so many had so little, it seemed odd to pity a princess, and yet Sarah did."

    old "She had known the girl for barely a moment, and to her surprise, began to see so much of herself in her."
    new "She had known the girl for barely a moment, and to her surprise, began to see so much of herself in her."

    old "Their lives, altough worlds apart, had been so similar. And if Bagrad fell, her life might be more similar than even Sarah wanted to admit."
    new "Their lives, altough worlds apart, had been so similar. And if Bagrad fell, her life might be more similar than even Sarah wanted to admit."

    old "Would they have been friends, if they had met when Sarah was still a princess?"
    new "Would they have been friends, if they had met when Sarah was still a princess?"

    old "Sarah shook her head to clear it."
    new "Sarah shook her head to clear it."

    old "She wasn't a child anymore, and she had no tolerance for childish thoughts."
    new "She wasn't a child anymore, and she had no tolerance for childish thoughts."

    old "There would be a battle tomorrow, and she could not afford to be distracted."
    new "There would be a battle tomorrow, and she could not afford to be distracted."

    old "The servant stopped and bowed low. With his arms he motioned for her to enter through the door to her room."
    new "The servant stopped and bowed low. With his arms he motioned for her to enter through the door to her room."

    old "As Sarah stepped into the room, she heard the door being closed behind her."
    new "As Sarah stepped into the room, she heard the door being closed behind her."

    old "The opulence of it nearly overwhelmed her."
    new "The opulence of it nearly overwhelmed her."

    old "Endless variations of gold, rubies and satin, crossed and weaved through one another."
    new "Endless variations of gold, rubies and satin, crossed and weaved through one another."

    old "Near the corner stood an enormous bed, covered in a rich thick purpura coloured blanket."
    new "Near the corner stood an enormous bed, covered in a rich thick purpura coloured blanket."

    old "Sarah could not help but smile as she looked at it."
    new "Sarah could not help but smile as she looked at it."

    old "Life with Xan was interesting, but it was also harsh and minimalistic."
    new "Life with Xan was interesting, but it was also harsh and minimalistic."

    old "He would never stand for such extravagence, and Sarah had adapted to that way of life."
    new "He would never stand for such extravagence, and Sarah had adapted to that way of life."

    old "But now, seeing something so rich, she wanted to enjoy it. Despite everything, it still came natural to her."
    new "But now, seeing something so rich, she wanted to enjoy it. Despite everything, it still came natural to her."

    old "Sarah quickly threw off her robes."
    new "Sarah quickly threw off her robes."

    old "Sarah let herself fall into the bed."
    new "Sarah let herself fall into the bed."

    old "At every edge of her body, she could feel the silky touch of the sheets wrapping around her."
    new "At every edge of her body, she could feel the silky touch of the sheets wrapping around her."

    old "It felt to her as if she was sinking into the bed, deeper and deeper."
    new "It felt to her as if she was sinking into the bed, deeper and deeper."

    old "She shifted around a bit, keeping herself from dissapearing into the bed entirely, and observed the room."
    new "She shifted around a bit, keeping herself from dissapearing into the bed entirely, and observed the room."

    old "Above her, the majestic ceilings depicted a tableau of a great battle, featuring hundreds of painstakingly painted figures."
    new "Above her, the majestic ceilings depicted a tableau of a great battle, featuring hundreds of painstakingly painted figures."

    old "Sarah didn't know too much of Bagrad's history and couldn't identify what battle it was supposed to be."
    new "Sarah didn't know too much of Bagrad's history and couldn't identify what battle it was supposed to be."

    old "Given the labour that had gone into this work, the battle must have been important. And still it meant nothing to her."
    new "Given the labour that had gone into this work, the battle must have been important. And still it meant nothing to her."

    old "The realization made Sarah sad, sad in the way that most of Bagrad made her sad."
    new "The realization made Sarah sad, sad in the way that most of Bagrad made her sad."

    old "It wasn't an overt sadness, but rather a sort of omnipresent depression. As if the very bricks in the wall ached with tiredness."
    new "It wasn't an overt sadness, but rather a sort of omnipresent depression. As if the very bricks in the wall ached with tiredness."

    old "Could a place long to die?"
    new "Could a place long to die?"

    old "If there could be such a place, this must be it, Sarah concluded."
    new "If there could be such a place, this must be it, Sarah concluded."

    old "Sarah wiped a tear away from her face."
    new "Sarah wiped a tear away from her face."

    old "Why was this happening. She hadn't cried in years, and now twice in the same day."
    new "Why was this happening. She hadn't cried in years, and now twice in the same day."

    old "Get it together."
    new "Get it together."

    old "Sarah pressed her hands across her face as if to force physically what she could not emotionally."
    new "Sarah pressed her hands across her face as if to force physically what she could not emotionally."

    old "A soft sound came from across the room. It was like the grinding of metal, yet somehow muted."
    new "A soft sound came from across the room. It was like the grinding of metal, yet somehow muted."

    old "Sarah quickly sat up."
    new "Sarah quickly sat up."

    old "It took her mind a moment to make sense of what her eyes could see."
    new "It took her mind a moment to make sense of what her eyes could see."

    old "Off towards the other side of the room the walls, once solid, now slowly parted."
    new "Off towards the other side of the room the walls, once solid, now slowly parted."

    old "Sarah reached out, gathering energy from her surroundings, ready to release whatever magic she'd need."
    new "Sarah reached out, gathering energy from her surroundings, ready to release whatever magic she'd need."

    old "But she wouldn't need any."
    new "But she wouldn't need any."

    old "Coming through the secret door was Samayra."
    new "Coming through the secret door was Samayra."

    old "Samayra, you almost gave me a heart atack!"
    new "Samayra, you almost gave me a heart atack!"

    old "The princess seemed genuinely apologetic."
    new "The princess seemed genuinely apologetic."

    old "I'm sorry, I'm sorry."
    new "I'm sorry, I'm sorry."

    old "She was franctically waving her hands around in an attempted gesture of apology."
    new "She was franctically waving her hands around in an attempted gesture of apology."

    old "Sarah crawled out of the bed."
    new "Sarah crawled out of the bed."

    old "You know, it's actually very bad idea to sneak up on a mage."
    new "You know, it's actually very bad idea to sneak up on a mage."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah could see that Samayra looked almost frozen with fear."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah could see that Samayra looked almost frozen with fear."

    old "I...I'm...so...sorry, I didn't know...you were..."
    new "I...I'm...so...sorry, I didn't know...you were..."

    old "I was just joking, I wouldn't hurt you."
    new "I was just joking, I wouldn't hurt you."

    old "But it wasn't that, Sarah now realized. She was more shocked of Sarah's nakedness than any magical threats."
    new "But it wasn't that, Sarah now realized. She was more shocked of Sarah's nakedness than any magical threats."

    old "Having lived an isolated life all these years, Sarah suddenly realized she had to some degree unlearned the social rules of her society."
    new "Having lived an isolated life all these years, Sarah suddenly realized she had to some degree unlearned the social rules of her society."

    old "Ooh, I forgot I wasn't wearing my robes."
    new "Ooh, I forgot I wasn't wearing my robes."

    old "No, I'm sorry, I shouldn't have just come in here like this, I'll leave, forgive me."
    new "No, I'm sorry, I shouldn't have just come in here like this, I'll leave, forgive me."

    old "Sarah walked up and grabbed Samayra's wrists before she could turn to leave."
    new "Sarah walked up and grabbed Samayra's wrists before she could turn to leave."

    old "Don't worry about it. It's fine. I don't mind if you don't mind."
    new "Don't worry about it. It's fine. I don't mind if you don't mind."

    old "Sarah could see Samayra trying to force herself to be comfortable. She did a poor job."
    new "Sarah could see Samayra trying to force herself to be comfortable. She did a poor job."

    old "Oh...oke...if you are, then...I can be..."
    new "Oh...oke...if you are, then...I can be..."

    old "Sarah was eager to change the subject, hoping to calm Samayra down by changing the subject."
    new "Sarah was eager to change the subject, hoping to calm Samayra down by changing the subject."

    old "How did you get in here anyway?"
    new "How did you get in here anyway?"

    old "Sarah saw her face light up."
    new "Sarah saw her face light up."

    old "Ooh, it was really quite easy."
    new "Ooh, it was really quite easy."

    old "Samayra walked back towards the passage at the other end of the room that had appeared."
    new "Samayra walked back towards the passage at the other end of the room that had appeared."

    old "It's a secret passage, honestly, the palace is full of them."
    new "It's a secret passage, honestly, the palace is full of them."

    old "I spend most of my youth exploring every inch of the palace, sneaking through tunnels, seeing where everything leads."
    new "I spend most of my youth exploring every inch of the palace, sneaking through tunnels, seeing where everything leads."

    old "Sarah studied the passage."
    new "Sarah studied the passage."

    old "Castle Reinmeer had secrets of its own, but nothing as sophisticated as this."
    new "Castle Reinmeer had secrets of its own, but nothing as sophisticated as this."

    old "Where does it lead?"
    new "Where does it lead?"

    old "Anywhere you want to, really. I took this one all the way from my room."
    new "Anywhere you want to, really. I took this one all the way from my room."

    old "But it can take you to the throne room, the council, the gardens, the kitchens even."
    new "But it can take you to the throne room, the council, the gardens, the kitchens even."

    old "It really just depends where you want."
    new "It really just depends where you want."

    old "Sarah listened. Whenever Samayra had a topic she liked to talk about, her voice would gradually shift towards one of excitement, rather than her natural nervousness."
    new "Sarah listened. Whenever Samayra had a topic she liked to talk about, her voice would gradually shift towards one of excitement, rather than her natural nervousness."

    old "Can you show me?"
    new "Can you show me?"

    old "The passage intrigued Sarah. Not to mention, she was sure that somewhere in this tunnels was the vault they were looking for."
    new "The passage intrigued Sarah. Not to mention, she was sure that somewhere in this tunnels was the vault they were looking for."

    old "Could you show me?"
    new "Could you show me?"

    old "Samayra nodded enthusiastically."
    new "Samayra nodded enthusiastically."

    old "Of course! Follow me."
    new "Of course! Follow me."

    old "Sarah followed Samayra through the passage, into the secret pathways of the palace."
    new "Sarah followed Samayra through the passage, into the secret pathways of the palace."

    old "The tunnels tolerated no light of any kind."
    new "The tunnels tolerated no light of any kind."

    old "There were no torches, no braziers, nothing that could ward this opressive darkness."
    new "There were no torches, no braziers, nothing that could ward this opressive darkness."

    old "Nothing, except for the braces on Samayara's wrists."
    new "Nothing, except for the braces on Samayara's wrists."

    old "In the light, they had shimmered as gold, but to Sarah's surprise, they shimmered as gold in the darkness as well, casting a soft yellow glow over the cold alabaster stone."
    new "In the light, they had shimmered as gold, but to Sarah's surprise, they shimmered as gold in the darkness as well, casting a soft yellow glow over the cold alabaster stone."

    old "Stick close to me, you can easily get lost in these tunnels, and without a source of light you'll never find your way out."
    new "Stick close to me, you can easily get lost in these tunnels, and without a source of light you'll never find your way out."

    old "Sarah did as she was told."
    new "Sarah did as she was told."

    old "It wasn't only a darkness that held dominion over these secret tunnels, there was also an odd chill in the air."
    new "It wasn't only a darkness that held dominion over these secret tunnels, there was also an odd chill in the air."

    old "Most of Bagrad was warmed by the war desert air but in these tunnels the air seemed stale, as if the desert could not reach it. As if nothing could."
    new "Most of Bagrad was warmed by the war desert air but in these tunnels the air seemed stale, as if the desert could not reach it. As if nothing could."

    old "Sarah watched Samayra. Her confident stride was the only thing that made Sarah somewhat comfortable."
    new "Sarah watched Samayra. Her confident stride was the only thing that made Sarah somewhat comfortable."

    old "The girl wore the same revealing dress she had worn earlier."
    new "The girl wore the same revealing dress she had worn earlier."

    old "Sarah had taken some time to get used to it, but in Bagrad, the fashion was decidedly more free than in Rosanna."
    new "Sarah had taken some time to get used to it, but in Bagrad, the fashion was decidedly more free than in Rosanna."

    old "Sarah could only imagine what her own father would have said if she had decided to wear something like that."
    new "Sarah could only imagine what her own father would have said if she had decided to wear something like that."

    old "But it also drew her in, in ways that Sarah herself found hard to be conscious of. She sometimes found herself staring at the princess, her flawless features, her lithe frame."
    new "But it also drew her in, in ways that Sarah herself found hard to be conscious of. She sometimes found herself staring at the princess, her flawless features, her lithe frame."

    old "Samayra was a hard person not to look at."
    new "Samayra was a hard person not to look at."

    old "For a moment, Sarah imagined seeing the faint glow of starlight, crowning Samayra's head."
    new "For a moment, Sarah imagined seeing the faint glow of starlight, crowning Samayra's head."

    old "Here, off to the left, and down this spiral."
    new "Here, off to the left, and down this spiral."

    old "Sarah had long given up any attempt to keep track of the maze she now found herself in."
    new "Sarah had long given up any attempt to keep track of the maze she now found herself in."

    old "With each twist, turn and stairway, Samayra guided her deeper into spaces within spaces. The palace, grand as it was, was in truth, grander still."
    new "With each twist, turn and stairway, Samayra guided her deeper into spaces within spaces. The palace, grand as it was, was in truth, grander still."

    old "After some time, Sarah and Samayra finally came upon the room that Samayra had intended to show her."
    new "After some time, Sarah and Samayra finally came upon the room that Samayra had intended to show her."

    old "Samayra turned back to Sarah."
    new "Samayra turned back to Sarah."

    old "She waved her hand towards a massive, solid metal door, as if to introduce it."
    new "She waved her hand towards a massive, solid metal door, as if to introduce it."

    old "The thing was made out of solid metal. The thing appeared to not only reflected no light, but seemed to instead absorb the light around it."
    new "The thing was made out of solid metal. The thing appeared to not only reflected no light, but seemed to instead absorb the light around it."

    old "Inscribed into its surface were incantations and symbols."
    new "Inscribed into its surface were incantations and symbols."

    old "Sarah could feel it resonate, alive with magic."
    new "Sarah could feel it resonate, alive with magic."

    old "The vault."
    new "The vault."

    old "That's what you and the wizard came here for, right?"
    new "That's what you and the wizard came here for, right?"

    old "Sarah found Samayra looking at her, defiantly."
    new "Sarah found Samayra looking at her, defiantly."

    old "We did, yes."
    new "We did, yes."

    old "My father promised you access, but he's playing a dangerous game."
    new "My father promised you access, but he's playing a dangerous game."

